    en: "Residents of nursing homes and adult care facilities in New York have extensive rights under both federal and state law — including the right to dignity, the right to be free from abuse and neglect, the right to participate in care decisions, and the right to complain without retaliation. When these rights are violated, there are specific agencies to contact."
